EDUCATIONAL AND TRANSFORMATIVE LEARNING NOTICE:

This work represents original research in Inquiry Methodology Framework for 
transformative question-based learning in the AI age.

ACADEMIC AND EDUCATIONAL USE:
When using this framework for academic, educational, or research purposes, please cite:

Handa, S. (2025). Inquiry Methodology Framework: Transformative Question-Based 
Learning for AI Age Adaptation. GitHub Repository. 
https://github.com/hand-shinya/inquiry-methodology-framework

EDUCATIONAL INSTITUTIONS AND PRACTITIONERS:
Schools, universities, training organizations, and educational practitioners are 
encouraged to use this framework for:
- Curriculum design and instructional methodology development
- Teacher and educator professional development
- Student learning pathway design and assessment
- Critical thinking and inquiry skill development programs

ORGANIZATIONAL DEVELOPMENT AND TRAINING:
Corporations, non-profits, and other organizations may freely use this framework for:
- Employee training and professional development
- Team building and collaborative learning initiatives
- Change management and organizational transformation
- Leadership development and strategic planning

PERSONAL GROWTH AND COACHING:
Individual practitioners, coaches, mentors, and personal development facilitators 
are encouraged to use this framework for:
- Personal reflection and growth processes
- Coaching and mentoring methodologies
- Self-directed learning and skill development
- Life planning and decision-making support

COMMUNITY AND SOCIAL TRANSFORMATION:
Community organizations and social change agents may adapt this framework for:
- Public dialogue and democratic engagement
- Conflict resolution and bridge-building
- Community problem-solving and collaborative action
- Cultural exchange and mutual understanding

INTEGRATION WITH THEORETICAL ECOSYSTEM:
This framework is designed to work in conjunction with:
- AI-Augmented Dialectics Theory (AADT) for cognitive foundations
- Comprehensive Intellectual Ownership Paradigm (CIOP) for social institution design
- Eastern philosophical contemplative practices
- Modern evidence-based educational methodologies

When implementing comprehensive solutions that integrate multiple frameworks, 
please acknowledge the interconnected nature of these theoretical contributions.

IMPLEMENTATION SHARING:
We encourage practitioners to share case studies, adaptation experiences, and 
implementation insights with the broader learning community to advance the field 
of transformative education and human development.

ATTRIBUTION GUIDANCE:
While commercial use is permitted under this license, we request that significant 
implementations include attribution and consider contributing improvements back 
to the open source community for the benefit of learners worldwide.